o-residents-apprehend-two-men-after-hypnotizing-their-victim-and-taking-all-he-had-in-lagos.jpg?w=1280&amp;ssl=1 1280w" sizes="(max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px" data-recalc-dims="1" /> Two elderly men have been reportedly nabbed for allegedly hypnotizing an innocent boy and collecting all the money he had on him. The incident occurred at Abule Egba area of Lagos state where the victim was reportedly approached by the men claimed to be basketball players. It would have been a stress-free and successful operation but the plan was foiled by some residents of the community who noticed the fishy act and rescued the victim from being robbed. A Facebook user, Salawu Ajokeade shared the story on her Facebook timeline with videos and pictures She wrote: “MAY GOD HELP US DIS EMBER PERIOD, THIS JUST HAPPENED CLOSE TO MY SHOP AT ABULE EGBA.THese 2 ELDERLY MEN WERE NABBED TRYING TO SCAM A GUY CLAIMING THEY ARE BASKETBALL STARS, THEY COLLECTED ALL THE CASH WIT HIM AND ASKED HIM TO GET HIS ATM…..FORTUNATELY FOR HIM,NEIGHBOURS AROUND NOTICED SOMEFIN FISHY AND STARTED SHOUTING THIEF AND THE BOY SENSES CAME BACK TO NORMAL. THEY HAVE BEEN ARRESTED AND TAKEN TO THE STATION…LET’S BE CAREFUL OUT THERE PLS AND BE WATCHFUL.”   Vanguard Nigeria News It was while she was still trying to find a convenient spot to hide that she was hit by stray bullets; she fell unconscious at the spot in her pool of blood February 28, 2017 In "Metro" Lagos—Operatives of the Lagos State Criminal Investigation and Intelligence Department, SCIID, Yaba, are currently investigating the death of a middle-aged man, identified as Anuoluwapo Saheed, who was reportedly stabbed to death at a hotel in Abule Egba area of Lagos. August 6, 2015 In "News" The name Sambisa forest, does not only ring a bell in Nigeria on a negative note. It also elicits cold shivers down the spine of anyone who has had an encounter with it- be he a Military man, victim of terrorists held hostage in the forest or residents within its… March 18, 